Metaphone PTBR

How to INSTALL (from source)

* for PHP 5
  go to php5 directory and you would do:
  $ phpize5
  $ ./configure
  $ make
  # make install

  Now you can enable it on php.ini, by adding this line:
  extension=metaphoneptbr.so


* for PostgreSQL
  go to pgsql directory and:
  $ make
  # make install
  
  Restart your server. Then, to install on you database:
  $ psql -d [your base] -f /usr/share/postgresql/8.3/contrib/metaphoneptbr.sql

  Now you can use the metaphone_ptbr() function:
  psql# SELECT metaphone_ptbr('Ola mundo');


* for command line program
  go to the 'source' directory, then:
  $ make
  # make install


* making debian packages
  PS: lembrar de trocar a vers√£o no arquivo debian/compat
  Inside the root metaphoneptbr directory (from source), run:
  # dpkg-buildpackage -rfakeroot -ICVS -tc  -D 

  It should produce some files like those, so far:
  ../metaphoneptbr_1.3_amd64.changes
  ../metaphoneptbr_1.3.dsc
  ../metaphoneptbr_1.3.tar.gz
  ../metaphoneptbr4pgsql_1.3_amd64.deb
  ../metaphoneptbr-utils_1.3_amd64.deb
  ../php5-metaphoneptbr_1.3_amd64.deb

